<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Indonesia's Bengkulu Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- A tectonic earthquake measuring
5.6 on the Richter scale jolted Indonesia's Bengkulu Province at
11.56 a.m. local time on Monday, reported Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Head of the local Geophysical Station Armien Paimin was quoted
as saying that the epicenter of the quake was located in the
Indian Ocean, some 30 kilometers west of South Bengkulu district,
at a depth of 33 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake caused panic among residents, especially those
working in storeyed buildings, the report said.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report of casualties and material loss
caused by the quake.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on July 17, a tectonic earthquake measuring 5.0 on the
Richter scale also jolted parts of Bengkulu Province. Another
earthquake measuring 5.1 on the Richter scale hit Bengkulu on July
29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
