<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African Non-commissioned Officer Kills 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 24 (Xinhua) -- A South African
non-commissioned officer shot dead five of his platoon members
and seriously injured two on a farm in the early hours of Monday,
South African Press Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The victims were apparently asleep when the officer shot them,
SAPA quoted the South African National Defense Force (SANDF) as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Those involved were all members of an infantry battalion, and
were doing a border control operation on the farm in the Free
State province.
</P>
<P>
They had set up a temporary camp on the farm.
</P>
<P>
The shooting took place at about 3.30 a.m. (0130 GMT), and the
officer handed himself over to local police about two and a half
hours later.
</P>
<P>
The SANDF said it would conduct an inquiry into the shooting
along with the police investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
