<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Raise American Air Strikes in U.N. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Foreign Minister
Sartaj Aziz Monday said Pakistan will raise the American air
strikes on Afghanistan and violation of Pakistan air space in the
United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Sartaj told the Senate that the Foreign Ministry has instructed
Pakistani Permanent Representative at the U.N. to take up the
violation of the country's space during the U.S. missile attacks
on Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has also sent a letter to the president of the U.N.
Security Council, protesting against the violation of Pakistan's
air space during the American missile attack on Afghanistan,
Sartaj said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. forces attacked with cruise missiles six sites in
Afghanistan, located close to the Pakistani border, which are
believed to be the hideouts of the anti-American Saudi millionaire
Osama bin Ladin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
