<HEADLINE> 3M Mozambican Kids to Be Vaccinated Against Polio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Prime Minister
Pascoal Mocumbi declared the beginning of the first phase of the
national anti-polio campaign here Monday.
</P>
<P>
During the two-phase campaign, three million children under
the age of five years will be vaccinated.
</P>
<P>
The first phase will end Friday when the second one will
start. The second phase will end on October 2.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi called on the parents around him to encourage others
to bring their children to the vaccination centers. In Catebe
Town in suburban Maputo, the Mozambican prime minister who was
formerly a doctor gave several children the drops against polio.
</P>
<P>
In order to mobilize the parents to participate in the drive,
the Mozambican government, the mass organizations and some
non-governmental organizations both at home and abroad have done
a lot in raising mass awareness and starting mobilization.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican government is aiming to eradicate polio before
2000. The last three cases of polio occurred in 1993 in which
one child died.
</P>
<P>
According to Radio Mozambique, First Lady Marcelina Chissano
Monday also officiated the launching of anti-polio drive in
Marracuene County of Maputo Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
