<HEADLINE> Istanbul Stock Exchange Index Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Istanbul Stock Exchange
National-100 Index closed at 3,292.75 Monday, down 79.53 points,
or 2.38 percent, from that of Friday.
</P>
<P>
The value of shares changed hands stood at over 40 trillion
Turkish Liras (146 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The financial index went down 99.81 points, or 2.41 percent, to
close at 4,061.80 points. The industrial index tumbled 66 points,
or 2.32 percent, to close at 2,792 points, while the service index
dived 85.18 points, or 2.03 percent to close at 4,112.49 points
from Friday's finishes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
