<HEADLINE> Poor Infrastructure Hinders Uganda's Development: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Lack of a well-developed
telecommunication infrastructure is affecting the efficiency of
all social and business interactions, thus hindering the
development of the country, a Ugandan minister said Monday.
</P>
<P>
John Nasasira, the minister of works, housing and
communications, said this here when opening the Second African
Regional Workshop on Communications, Radio Uganda reported.
