Movements of people over large distances, usually at a high
cost of time and transport, result in low efficiency, Nasasira
asserted.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan government will try to ensure all social members
can have easy access to good telecommunications so as to
facilitate industrialization and economic progress in the
country.
</P>
<P>
In the information age, development of telecommunications is
of paramount importance for most African countries, the Ugandan
minister said, adding that effective and continued development
can only be achieved with the concerted efforts of the private
sector, training institutions and professional associations.
</P>
</TEXT>
