<P>
Israel since Monday tightened security at Ben Gurion
International Airport and other strategic sites for fear of
terrorist attacks.
</P>
<P>
This measure was taken after receiving warnings that certain
Islamic groups are planning to target U.S. and Israeli airports
and other strategic places, including bombing foreign airlines in
Israel, in retaliation against U.S. missile attacks on Sudan and
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, the U.S. conducted cruise missiles strikes at
targets in Sudan and Afghanistan that the U.S. believed to have
been the terrorist basis involved in the bombings of two
U.S. embassies in Africa early this month.
</P>
<P>
Israel is one of the countries voiced strong support to the
U.S. air strikes. But most of the Arab and Islamic countries,
including Palestine, termed the air strikes as provocative action
against the Muslims. 
