<HEADLINE> Iranian Leader Condemns U.S. Attacks in Sudan, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei condemned on Monday the recent U.S. missile attacks
in Sudan and Afghanistan, terming the attacks as an explicit
example of state terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the Iranian cabinet members on the occasion of the
Government Week, Khamenei said that what happened in Sudan and
Afghanistan last Thursday is unacceptable to the peoples of the
world.
</P>
<P>
It is unacceptable that a government relying on its military
might attacks another country and kills the defenseless people,
the official news agency IRNA quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei termed the U.S. missile attacks as a criminal act,
