<HEADLINE> Nicol Struggles into Second Round in HK Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 25 (Xinhua) -- World number one Peter Nicol
of Scotland struggled for a second round berth in the 74,000 U.S.
dollars Hong Kong Open squash tournament on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Nicol came back from a game down to fought back talented world
number 23 Amr Shabana of Egypt 14-15, 15-12, 15-12, 15-7.
</P>
<P>
Nicol will face the winner of Wednesday's first round match
between second seed Jansher Khan of Pakistan and Faheem Khan of
Hong Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani ace, 29, is seeking for his 100th title of his
career since he won his first title in September 1986.
</P>
<P>
Squash will be a medal sport for the first time in next
month's Commonwealth Games.
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's other first round matches, Australian World Open
Champion Rodney Eyles, fourth seed here, disposed of England's
Nicholas Taylor 15-17, 15-11, 15-11, 15-7. 
