<HEADLINE> EU Approves Acquisition of Rolls Royce by Volkswagen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
executive body of the European Union, gave its approval on Tuesday
for the acquisition of Rolls Royce/Bentley and Cosworth by
Volkswagen.
</P>
<P>
The acquisition will not raise any competition concerns because
of the limited market shares of Rolls Royce/Bentley and Cosworth,
said commission spokeswoman, Martine Reicherts.
</P>
<P>
The overlap of Volkswagen and Cosworth's car engine
manufacturing activities will not create any impediment to
competition in the market for car engines either, commission
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The commission agreed that Volkswagen will manufacture and
distribute luxury cars under the Bentley name immediately, and
will continue to do so after January 1, 2003, and that BMW has
granted Volkswagen a license to use the name for a limited period
until December 31, 2002. 
</P>
