<HEADLINE> EC Food Security Aid to Dhaka Reaches 80,000 Tons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC) has
ended its 1998 food aid program to Bangladesh by contributing a
total of 89 million taka (about 1.89 million U.S. dollars), the
latest issue of Economic Times weekly reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In all, the EC delivered 81,375 tons of wheat this year at a
cost of 61 million taka (about 1.3 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Over and above its deliveries in kind, it has committed
additional 28 million taka (about 6 million dollars) in cash for
food security program implemented by the government and local
non-government organizations (NGOs).
</P>
<P>
The wheat grant will be used by the Bangladeshi government in
the following ways: 30.000 tons for free distribution in the
Vulnerable Groups Development Program; 25,000 tons for
food-for-workers activities under the Rural Development Program
and 21,375 tons for the Integrated Food-Assisted Development
Program.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 5,000 tons will go to Bangladesh NGO Institute of
Integrated Rural Development. 
</P>
