<HEADLINE> Training Class on Male Reproductive Disease Held in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 25 (Xinhua) -- More than 110 doctors from both
China and abroad gathered here today to attend an advanced
training class on treating male reproductive disease with
traditional Chinese medical methods.
</P>
<P>
The class was held in the Tianjin Heping Hospital of
Traditional Chinese Medicine, where hundreds of thousand of
patients suffering from this malady have been cured in the past
dozen years.
</P>
<P>
According to experts from the World Health Organization (WHO),
men's reproductive disease, after cancer and heart disease, may
become a major problem threatening human health in the next
century.
</P>
<P>
Experts warn that the quality of male sperm is
decreasing, with sperm density reduced from 113 million per
liter in 1940 to 66 million per liter in 1990, while the average
amount of sperm discharged each time dropped from 3.4 ml to 2.75
ml.
</P>
<P>
Experts attribute this decline mainly to pollution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
