<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Sees High Growth in Passenger, Cargo Flow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The Macao International Airport
(MIA) scored an increase in both passenger and cargo flow in July
this year, according to an MIA press release issued Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The monthly number of passenger arrivals reached the highest
level of 205,595 following the peak of 189,925 in May of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Passengers to and from Taiwan and the inland areas of China
constitute 93 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Cargo handled in July represented a sharp increase of 224
percent compared with that in July last year.
</P>
<P>
The unusual and considerable growth in air cargo was due to the
hindrances in the beginning of operations of the new Hong Kong
Airport, MIA sources said. 
