you didn't do," O'Neill was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
"When I won my Olympic gold it was my seventh event. It was
also the only time that week he didn't tell me after a race that
I could have done better. He should know that I don't find any of
that stuff motivating," she said.
</P>
<P>
O'Neill also said after her failure to win a 200-meter
butterfly event in Europe Talbot also blasted her.
</P>
<P>
"He yelled at Scott about me -- on and on and on about how
every race I've had in the last four years has been too easy, and
now that's caught up with me, and I won't win again unless I
improve things he pointed out," she said.
</P>
<P>
The timing of these comments certainly would not help the
Australian swimming as the national team arrived in Perth on
Tuesday for a training camp for the Commenwealth Games.
</P>
<P>
