<HEADLINE> 1 Million Australian Households Have </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- About 1 million Australian
homes, or 14 percent of all households in Australia, are hooked up
to the Internet, according to official figures released here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The number of households with Internet access grew by 14
percent between February and May, a survey by the Australian
Bureau of Statistics (ABS) found.
</P>
<P>
The ABS said more than 970,000 households had home Internet
access, representing 14 percent of all households and 34 percent
of the households with computers.
</P>
<P>
It said the bulk of the increase was in households which
already had computers.
</P>
<P>
The ABS said 94 percent of the adults accessing the Internet
from home used it once a week or more often.
</P>
<P>
The ABS said 409,000 adults bought goods and services over the
Internet in the 12 months to May.  
