<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Dialog to Safeguard Regional Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami called Tuesday for dialog to safeguard peace and stability
in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Dialog is the "most rational way" to remove tension and crisis
and forge peace and stability, Khatami told visiting Armenian
Foreign Minister Vardan Oskanyan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he insisted the dialog be based on principles of
mutual respect and non-interference in the internal affairs of
other countries.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president rejected the presence of outside forces
in Central Asia and the Caucasus, saying that Israel's influence
in the region has sparked Iran's concern.
</P>
<P>
Iran, a leading rival of Israel, will never tolerate influence
and domination of the Jewish state in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the relations between Iran and Armenia, Khatami
said that friendly bilateral relations are needed in promoting
development and progress.
</P>
<P>
He voiced Iran's readiness to boost the ties and conduct
cooperation on the bilateral and regional levels.
</P>
<P>
Oskanyan, who arrived here Monday for a two-day visit,
expressed support for Iran's policies, saying Iran plays a key
role in maintaining the regional peace and stability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
