<HEADLINE> Nanjing Hosts Exhibition on Life of H.C.Andersen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- An art exhibition on the life of
Hans Christian Andersen, the world-renouned Danish creator of
fairy tales, opened today in this capital of east China's Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
The one-week exhibition will display 200 photos featuring
literary works, paintings, and paper-cuts depicting the life
of Andersen and his famous fairy tales.
</P>
<P>
Andersen was born into a poor family early in the 18th century. He
wrote over 160 fairy tales including the "The Little Match Girl" and
"The Ugly Duckling," stories long beloved by both children and
adult readers around the world.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is being sponsored by the provincial cultural
department and foreign affairs office.  
