<HEADLINE> New Zealanders Warned Not to Travel to Muslim Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 25 (Xinhua) -- New Zealanders have been
warned not to travel to Afghanistan, Sudan, Egypt, Pakistan and
the Persian Gulf states.
</P>
<P>
In a notice issued Tuesday by the Foreign Affairs and Trade
Ministry, New Zealand nationals were warned that the situation has
become "increasingly tense and uncertain in those countries
following recent military action by the United States against
terrorist targets in Afghanistan and Sudan."
</P>
<P>
There have been "public demonstrations in Muslim countries
against the actions of the United States," said the notice.
</P>
<P>
"Although there is no specific threat to New Zealand nationals
in these countries, New Zealanders living in or traveling to these
regions should remain alert."
</P>
<P>
The notice also urged New Zealand nationals to take sensible
security precautions and review the necessity to travel to those
regions. 
</P>
