<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices closed lower on
the Singapore Stock Market Tuesday although calmer regional
currencies and a rebound in Western bourses soothed the market
somewhat.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Industrial Index (STII) lost 5.99
points to end at 911.32.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover increased to 141.71 million units valued at
140.19 million Singapore dollars (about 79.65 million U.S.
dollars). There were 140 gainers against 122 losers with 327
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
M Res was the most active stock of the day as it closed on a
turnover of 16.20 million units. It was followed by NBT that had
13.38 million stocks traded. DBS Land was next with 6.60 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture was the top gainer of the day as it gained 18 cents to
end at 4.52 Singapore dollars. Genting edged up 16 cents to finish
at 3.34 Singapore dollars. SIA F inched up 15 cents to end at
6.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Metalock was the biggest loser of the day as
it lost 75 cents to 0.50 Singapore dollars at close. Creative 50
shed 40 cents to finish at 19.20 Singapore dollars. Jurship went
down by 20 cents to end at 7.70 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
