<HEADLINE> Canada to Restore Ties with Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Canada has decided to restore
relations with Nigeria, according to Nigeria's newly-appointed
Foreign Minister Lloyd Axworthy.
</P>
<P>
He said that Canadian Secretary of State for Africa David
Kilgour was scheduled to visit Nigeria next month and Canada
would sponsor a forum for pan-Commonwealth non-governmental
organizations, The Guardian newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Axworthy disclosed that Canada would offer financial and
technical assistance to Nigerian in support of the country's
transition to democracy.
</P>
<P>
Canada cut aid to Nigeria in 1995 and shut down its High
Commission last year when the late General Sani Abacha's
government was widely accused of human rights abuses and his
ambition to perpetuate dictatorship through a manipulated
political transition program.
</P>
<P>
With the renewed relations between Nigeria and Canada, the
report said, "the last frontiers of diplomatic hostility toward
Nigeria is crumbling." 
</P>
</TEXT>
