<HEADLINE> Yangtze River Flooding Causes Great Economic Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Flooding of the Yangtze River
since this summer had caused more than 38.4 billion yuan (4.6
billion US dollars) in direct economic losses to central China's
Hubei Province by 20th of this month, an official source said here
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The flooding, the worst since 1954, has affected 4.47 million
residents, damaged 2.54 million ha of cropland, and forced 9,769
enterprises to suspend or reduce production, Yang Yongliang,
deputy Secretary of the Hubei Provincial Committee of the
Communist Party of China, said at a news briefing today.  
</P>
