<HEADLINE> China's Flood Seasons to End in December If Typhoons Come Late </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- China's flood seasons will
probably last till December if typhoons come late, said an
official of the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The flood seasons will come to an end in October if weather
conditions are normal, the official also said, adding that the
high water level along the Yangtze River will remain for about 20
days and that on the Nenjiang and Songhua rivers will also take
two weeks to recede, on condition that there will be no torrential
rains or new flood peaks at upper reaches.
</P>
<P>
The water recession standard is set below the danger mark, he
said. China's flood seasons began in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
