<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Friendship with China Continues to Be Cornerstone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 25 (Xinhua) -- "Our abiding and time-tested
friendship with China will continue to be a cornerstone of our
foreign policy," Pakistani Foreign Minister Sartaj Aziz said in
his policy statement presented at the Senate Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Aziz, who assumed his office early this month, said that "we
attach the utmost priority to maintaining and further promoting
our relations with China."
</P>
<P>
Viewed in the light of dramatic global changes, the continuity
of Pakistan-China bilateral relations is "remarkable", "based on
complete trust and understanding, these ties are strong and
vibrant," Aziz said.
</P>
<P>
On Pakistan's relations with Russia, the foreign minister said,
"we have made a good beginning in establishing mutually beneficial
cooperation with Russia."
</P>
<P>
There had been several high level exchanges between Pakistan
and Russia, which should further strengthen the economic and
political cooperation between the two countries, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He also said that "Pakistan's relations with the Islamic world
will continue to be one of fundamental importance for us."
</P>
<P>
Pakistan had always played a crucial role in upholding Islamic
causes and promoting unity in the Islamic world, the foreign
minister said, adding that "this has been and will continue to be
a major pillar of our foreign policy." 
</P>
