<DOCNO> XIE19980825.0223 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xiamen to Mass-produce and Market Dell Computers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The port city of Xiamen in east
China's Fujian province will become one of the four permanent
production bases of the Dell Computer Corp. of the United States.
</P>
<P>
John J. Legere, president of Dell Computer Asia-Pacific, said
his company has drafted a long-term strategic plan for the
construction and development of this new production base.
</P>
<P>
China is the world's fastest growing computer market. It is
estimated that by the year 2002, China's PC market will be four
times what it is today, with some 10.6 million units on the market
by then, which will make it the largest market in the Asia-Pacific
region.
</P>
<P>
Dell Computer Corp., the world's leading direct marketer of
computer systems, began direct sales recently in China. Direct
computer sales is a two-tiered business operation based on a
direct relationship between the manufacturer and the customer,
without intermediaries such as distributors and retailers.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, Dell Computer Corp.'s direct
sales will have nine locations in such major Chinese cities as
Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
Customers can place order through telephone or on internet, and
receive Dell's "built-to-order" service which is uniform around
the world.
</P>
<P>
Dell Computer Corp. has founded a China customers center in
Xiamen, which combines production, marketing and customer hotline
service.
</P>
<P>
Dell Xiamen Company, with a registered investment of 15 million
U.S. dollars, now mass-produces desktops, laptops and servers,
targeted at the Chinese market, in its Xiamen production centers.
</P>
<P>
Sales of Dell products in China is still less than 100 million
U.S. dollars, but they will grow by 100 percent in the next
three to five years, said John J. Legere.
</P>
<P>
According to him, Dell recorded a 1997 turnover of 13.6 billion
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
