<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Cave Dwelling Found in Liaoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 25 (Xinhua) -- An 18,000-year-old cave
dwelling has been excavated in Xiuyan county in northeast China's
Liaoning province.
</P>
<P>
The cave, found by a local farmer who was digging a storage
space at the back of his house, is about 30 meters deep, 1.6-2.1
meters high, and 1.2-2.5 meters wide.
</P>
<P>
Animal bones weighing a total of 50 kilograms have been located
in the cave, and identified as bones of deer, oxen and bears.
</P>
<P>
Local paleontologists say the burnt bones were disposed of by
human beings living in the cave.
</P>
<P>
The experts say that this find will contribute to the study of
local ancestors as well as the ancient living environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
