<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed
lower here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 12 points lower at 1944 with a turnover
of 60
million NZ dollars (29.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Air New Zealand edged up 2 cents to 175 cents. AMP plummeted by
42
cents to 2,548 cents. Auckland Airport eased 3 cents to 202 cents.

Brierley Investments dipped 1 cent to 72 cents. Telecom fell 13
cents to
802 cents. Carter Holt Harvey gained 1 cent to 172 cents. Fletcher

Building shed 5 cents to 270 cents. Fletcher Forest was stable at
85
cents. Fletcher Paper also was steady at 150 cents. Fletcher
Energy rose
9 cents to 409 cents. 
</P>
