<HEADLINE> Modern Garbage Treatment Plant Operational in Guangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- A modern garbage treatment plant
has been put into operation in Beihai in south China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The plant, costing 130 million yuan, covers an area of 15.62
hectares and can dispose of 1,500 tons of garbage daily.
</P>
<P>
The plant has an expected service life of over 17 years and is
designed according to international standards. It has complete
systems that collect and treat wastewater and methane and conduct
environmental monitoring.  
</P>
</TEXT>
