<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, August 25 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK -- Talks between the United States and the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) held here on Friday and Monday
will continue into a third session Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
However, both sides have kept reporters guessing on the topics
of the discussion, except for a brief confirmation made by
U.S. delegation spokesman Richard Scorza who said the Agreed
Framework reached between both sides in 1994 was included in the
agenda. (US-DPRK-Dialogue)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
VIENNA -- The average price of OPEC's basket of seven crudes
rebounded slightly last week to 11.89 U.S. dollars from 11.60
dollars the week before, statistics released Monday by the
Vienna-based OPEC secretariat show.
</P>
<P>
Experts here say that a large market surplus is the root cause
of weak prices in the world crude markets. The Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) said efforts to decrease the
daily output ceiling in March and June yielded few results.
(OPEC-Oil Prices)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The U.N. Security Council Monday joined the
regional calls for an immediate cease-fire and the start of
negotiations toward a peaceful settlement of the conflict in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The council, after informal consultations, expressed support
for the regional diplomatic initiatives including the one of South
African President Nelson Mandela as the current chairman of the
Southern African Development Community, council President Danilo
Turk of Slovenia told reporters. (UN-Congo) 
</P>
