<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong Sees Brisk Housing Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 25 (Xinhua)--Shandong province, an economic
powerhouse in east China, sold 1.69 million square meters of
office and housing space in the first six months, a year-to-year
rise of 80 percent and the highest growth recorded in five years.
</P>
<P>
Real estate investment from state-owned companies amounted to
4.04 billion yuan (about 50 million U.S. dollars), up 28 percent,
also the highest rise in five years.
</P>
<P>
The development of residential projects stood out in the first
half, with investment and sales up 53.9 and 78 percent
respectively. Rising in demand also pushed up the average price to
1,282 yuan per square meter from the previous 1,217 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
