<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7th Yangtze Flood Crest Taking Shape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The 7th flood peak of the
Yangtze River has formed along the upper reaches and is expected
to pass Yichang of central China's Hubei Province tonight.
</P>
<P>
At the Cuntan Measuring Point of Chongqing Municipality in
southwest China, the water level reached 183.21 meters and had a
flow rate of 58,000 cubic meters per second, on Sunday at 16
hours, 1.1 meters higher and 3,100 cubic meters more than the
figures of the previous flood crest, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The new peak could bring more difficulties to flood-fighting in
downstream areas, an official of the State Flood Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters said here today at a related news
conference.  
</P>
</TEXT>
