<HEADLINE> Non-state High-tech Companies Booming in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Non-state high-tech companies
in central China's Henan Province turned out a total income of
11.67 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
These 4,149 companies now have a total property value of 10
billion yuan, with 14 of them realizing an annual income of more
than 100 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the companies invested 770 million yuan, or 6.6
percent of their income, in the development of new products, much
higher than other enterprises in the province.  
</P>
