<DOCNO> XIE19980825.0251 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Comets Beat Sting to Enter WNBA Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Two-time MVP Cynthia Cooper
scored 23 points to help the defending champions Houston Comets
advance to the WNBA finals with a 77-61 victory over the
Charlotte Sting in Houston on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The Comets swept two straight wins in the best-of-3 series and
will meet Cleveland in the showdowns. Cleveland nipped Phoenix
67-66 tonight to force the decisive final game. The two sides
fought a 1-1 tie and the third game will be held on Tuesday night
in Cleveland.
</P>
<P>
Sheryl Swoops netted 18 points and had 13 rebounds for the
Comets, while Tina Thompson had 12 points and 14 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
The Comets led 50-38 with 17 minutes left in the game, but the
Sting kept coming back after Andrea Stinson had six points during
a spurt to narrow the lead to 55-50 with 13:26 left.
</P>
<P>
The Comets, who won for the 15th time in 16 home games this
season, have beaten the Sting nine of the 10 times they've player
over the past two years.
</P>
<P>
In another semifinal, Jennifer Gillom displayed a brilliant
show tonight, scoring 27 points, but missed a 17-footer at the
buzzer as the Rockers pipped Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
Eastern Conference champion Cleveland is confident to enter
the final after winning this game. It was the Rockers' first
victory over Phoenix in four tries this season.
</P>
<P>
"It is goood to show everybody we can beat them," said
Michelle Edwards, who led the Rockers with 18 points. Isabella
Fijalkowsi had 16 points for Cleveland, and Janice Braxton
grabbed 10 rebounds including two crucial ones in the final
minute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
