<HEADLINE> CMC Vice-Chairman Meets Pakistani Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- General Zhang Wannian,
vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission (CMC), met here
today with visiting General Jehangir Karamat, chairman of the
Pakistani Joint Chiefs of Staff Committee and chief of the Army
Staff, and they exchanged views on issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that China and Pakistan are friendly neighbors and
that Sino-Pakistani relations have progressed smoothly since the
establishment of diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
Zhang pointed out that Sino-Pakistani relations have stood the
test of time based on the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
The relationship serves as a model as to how countries with
different social systems can successfully establish friendly
cooperative relations, according to Zhang.
</P>
<P>
He said frequent high-level visits between leaders of the two
countries will breathe new life into the development of bilateral
cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Karamat expressed admiration for the economic wonder China has
achieved in recent years, as well as gratitude for the support and
help the nation have provided for Pakistan in different periods.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed great satisfaction with the smooth progress
of Sino-Pakistani relations.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant General Qian Shugen, deputy chief of the PLA general
staff, and Inam Ul-haque, Pakistani ambassador to China, attended
the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
