<HEADLINE> Eastern Airlines Offers New Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai-based China Airlines
has announced that its passengers is now able to go through
boarding formalities ahead of time outside of airports.
</P>
<P>
To make things convenient for passengers, the company has set
up offices in downtown areas to issue boarding cards. In an
initial move, the company will provide such services to persons
taking flights after 12:00 am every day to Beijing, Guangzhou,
Shenzhen and Qingdao, according to a company official.
</P>
<P>
He also said that people who avail themselves of this new
service can entrust their luggage with the airline offices to take
on to the flight and told passengers not to put unsuitable objects
in their luggage. 
</P>
