<BODY>
<HEADLINE> University Establishes Software Joint Venture With Dutch Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 25 (Xinhua) -- NEU-Alpine Software Co. Ltd.
of Northeast University in Shenyang and the Baan Co, of the
Netherlands on Monday established a new software joint venture at
a cost of 2.5 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The agreement for NEU-Alpine, a listed software company, to
provide 60 percent of the investment, with the remainder coming
from Baan.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will supply Chinese enterprises with applied
software systems for management, planning, production, purchasing
and marketing.
</P>
<P>
Baan currently focuses on developing applied resource planning
software used by well over 4,000 businesses around the world,
including affiliates of Boeing and Mercedes-Benz, and numerous
Chinese companies. The company also offers consulting service.
</P>
<P>
NEU-Alpine, established on the basis of the university's
software center, operates more than 30 Chinese subsidiaries
engaged in software development and marketing.
</P>
<P>
The high-tech enterprise produces universal software
applications and platforms, as well as major professional software
applications and digital medical equipment.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch company plans to provide manpower and marketing
resources for the joint venture and NEU-Alpine will concentrate on
its enterprise management software business.  
</P>
</TEXT>
