<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Bank to Launch Plastic Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Janata Bank, one of Bangladesh's
four nationalized banks, will introduce plastic money, or credit
cards, under the name Janata Bank Ready Cash Card later this year.
</P>
<P>
"We have got the permission from the central bank and
formalities are almost finalized to launch the credit card during
the November-December period this year," Managing Director M.A.
Hashem of the Janata Bank was quoted as saying by the newspaper
The Financial Express on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bank, the country's first nationalized commercial bank to
issue credit cards, has entered into an agreement with American
Investment International Inc., Los Angeles, and has been
registered with the Board of Investment to introduce the plastic
money.
</P>
<P>
The Ready Cash Cards will be issued to Janata Bank account
holders against a balance to be fixed under mutual agreement and
each card holder will have a spending limit and be advised to
maintain that limit, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
A computerized central processing center will be established in
Bangladesh, with the capacity to create and personalize the cards,
receive data from the point of sale terminals, monitor
transactions, create and distribute report invoices and receive
and respond to customer service calls, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
