<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Stresses Ties with Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese-Russian relations will
further improve with the on-going Russia visit by President Tran
Duc Luong despite the recent change of administration in Russia,
said a Vietnamese Foreign Ministry spokesperson Monday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson delivered the message while answering
questions about the impact of the change in the Russian government.
</P>
<P>
He described the change as an internal affair of Russia and
expressed the belief that "the traditional friendly relations
between Vietnam and Russia will continue to be strengthened and
developed."
</P>
<P>
Luong's visit, at the invitation of Russian President Boris
Yeltsin, is taking place in accordance with the plan agreed upon
by the two sides, the spokesperson said, adding that "we hope the
visit will mark a new stage of development in the two countries'
relations."
</P>
<P>
During his five-day official visit starting Monday, Luong will
meet Yeltsin and other Russian officials.
</P>
<P>
Several cooperation agreements between Vietnam and Russia are
expected to be signed during the visit.
</P>
<P>
This is the first official visit to Russia by a Vietnamese
president since 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
