<HEADLINE> Men's Table Tennis World Cup to Be Held in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The 19th World Cup men's table
tennis tournament will be held in south China's Shantou from
October 15 to 18, the Chinese Table Tennis Association said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
China's Olympic gold medalist Liu Guoliang and former world
champion Kong Linghui, who won the World Cup in 1995 and 1996
respectively, will both seek a World Cup double in the annual
event which was inaugurated in 1980.
</P>
<P>
Ma Lin, a rising Chinese star, was also confirmed to take part
in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The entry of 16 include the five continental champions and the
top players in the world rankings. 
</P>
