<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Heroine of Disney's New Cartoon Found a Native of Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 25 (Xinhua) -- After years of study, Chinese
researchers have determined that the hometown of Hua Mulan, the heroine
of Walt Disney's newest cartoon film "Mulan," is in central China's
Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
Researchers believe that the heroine, whose real surname was Wei,
was born about 1,300 years ago in today's Yucheng County in Henan.
</P>
<P>
A tomb and a hall can still be seen there memorializing the
brave woman, who served in the army in place of her old and sickly
father. Her identity was kept secret until the war ended.
</P>
<P>
Many poets and writers through the ages have praised Mulan in
their works. In the memorial hall there are two stone tablets
telling of Mulan's life and exploits.
</P>
<P>
To memorize the ancient heroine, local people named a new
railway station, 2.5 k.m. from the memorial hall, as Mulan Station
in 1996. And several tourist companies in Henan are now busy
preparing tour grograms leading up to Mulan's hometown.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
