<HEADLINE> U.S. Pilot Rescued After F-16 Fighter Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 25 (Xinhua) -- A pilot of a U.S. Air Force F-16
fighter has been rescued after his plane crashed into the sea
about one kilometer from the coastal city of Kangnung in South
Korea.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened about 6:15 p.m. (local time) Monday while
the pilot, who is attached to the 36th Fighter Squadron at Osan
Air Base in South Korea, was on a routine training mission,
according to a news released by U.S. Troops Korea Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The pilot was rescued last night by a South Korean fishing boat
after he ejected from his plane.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is under investigation, said the news
release.
</P>
<P>
Three F-16 jet fighters have crashed in South Korea during the
past 18 months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
