<HEADLINE> Italian Employment Steady in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 24 (xinhua) -- Employment remained steady in large
Italian industries in May this year, but a drop of 2.3 percent was
reported for the preceding 12 months, the National Statistics
Institute (ISTAT) said in a press release on Monday.
</P>
<P>
During the first five months of this year, the number of jobs
fell by 1.5 percent compared to the same period in 1997, before
unemployment rates stabilized in May.
</P>
<P>
For the manufacturing industries alone, the decline was 1.8
percent for the first five months, while workers in this sector
drawing state unemployment benefits surged by 50 percent from May
1997 to May 1998.
</P>
<P>
A 1.5 percent increase in jobs were reported in manufacturing
in May, up from 0.2 percent in February.
</P>
<P>
However, a fall of 4.9 percent of jobs were reported in the
energy sector in May, because of a round of retirements in April.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the number of people on the payroll of large
service industries was up 0.1 percent in May, and down 0.2 percent
for the 12-month period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
