<HEADLINE> China's Ethnic Region Invests More in Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region, the smallest ethnic autonomous region in China, plans to
inject 10.2 billion yuan into infrastructure this year, up 20.6
percent from 1997.
</P>
<P>
The money will mainly go to telecommunications, agriculture,
and housing, according to Ma Qizhi, chairman of the Regional
People's Government, in an effort to attain its 8-percent growth
target of the year.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia covers a 51,800-sq.km. area and has a population of 4.9
million, 33 percent of whom are descendants of those who came from
the Middle East in the 13th century.
</P>
<P>
It has large amounts of mineral resources like coal, natural
gas, and petroleum, but is listed one of the most underdeveloped
areas in China.
</P>
<P>
This year, Ningxia has 22 key projects, including a natural gas
pipeline, an irrigation system, the largest to be built in the
country, and an expressway, the first in the autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
The region has also been upgrading 21 key enterprises to
improve capacity and competitiveness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
