<DOCNO> XIE19980825.0306 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Bank Manager in 300 Million Rupee Fraud </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 25 (Xinhua) -- A Bank of Ceylon manager and
his wife, also an employee of the same bank, have been arrested by
police for a 300 million rupee (4.55 million U.S. dollars) fraud,
the official newspaper Daily News reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bank manager had been siphoning out Bank funds over a
period of 10 years and with the money had been living a luxurious
life owning several vehicles including a Mercedes Benz and a
Pajero and several houses and holiday homes, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The suspect who worked in the clearing section of the bank, had
found a loophole whereby he could siphon out bank funds without
being discovered. He did so for 10 years out of the 20 years he
served in the state-owned Bank of Ceylon.
</P>
<P>
He had not touched the money of depositors but embezzled the
bank's own funds, police sources were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The manager, his wife and four other suspects who were produced
by police before a Colombo magistrate were remanded for offenses
under the Public Property Act. 
</P>
</TEXT>
