<HEADLINE> Brazil Chicken Exports Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's chicken exports
in July went up by 8.13 percent from June, according to the
Brazilian Association of Chicken exporters.
</P>
<P>
Brazil exported 51,100 tons of chicken meat in July and earned
63.7 million U.S. dollars, press reports quoted the association as
saying Monday.
</P>
<P>
July was the third month in a row that recorded a rise.
</P>
<P>
However, the country's chicken exports in the first seven
months this year were 10.45 percent less in volume and 22 percent
less in earnings than the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil exported a total of 340,800 tons of chicken worth 406.2
million dollars between January and July 1998. 
</P>
