<HEADLINE> Greece is Bulgaria's Door to EU, NATO: Kostov </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan
Kostov assessed the relations between his country and Greece on
the eve of his Wednesday visit to Greece.
</P>
<P>
"We are well aware that Greece is Bulgaria's door to the EU and
NATO," Kostov said in a interview with the Bulgarian National
Radio.
</P>
<P>
"We wish to make it clear to the Greek public that Bulgaria is
not interested in shortening the distance in its relations with
third countries at the expense of its relations with Greece," said
Kostov.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Kostov will discuss with his Greek
counterpart Kostas Simitis the location of three border crossings,
which the Bulgarian leader has indicated is a top issue on the
agenda for strengthening bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Other topics the two prime ministers will bring up include
bilateral measures to avoid double registration of the flow of
goods between the two countries and the the construction of the
Bourgas-Alexandroupolis pipeline.
</P>
<P>
The pipeline project, which is still under evaluation, will
extend from Burgas, a Bulgarian Black Sea port city, to
Alexandroupolis, in Greece by the Aegean Sea. 
</P>
