<HEADLINE> Things Look Rosy for '99 Garden Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Some 154 representatives from 62
countries and regions and 11 international organizations attended
a conference yesterday to discuss arrangements for the China '99
Kunming International Horticultural Expo, China Daily reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The expo, which opens next May, will be the last international
gala held in China this century.
</P>
<P>
The expo is supported by the Chinese Government and the
International Gardeners' Assn. Yunnan province has invested more
than one billion yuan (120 million U.S. dollars) preparing for it.
</P>
<P>
Construction of 80 percent of the expo buildings has been
completed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Kunming has decided to bring forward its urban
traffic plan for 2008 and complete it by May 1999.
</P>
<P>
By then, more than 20 roads will have been constructed or
renovated, grass and trees planted along 31 streets, and five big
garden squares set up.
</P>
<P>
Kunming airport will be extended to handle 10 million people a
year by the end of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The rapid progress in the construction of buildings for the
expo satisfied the representatives from various countries.
</P>
<P>
Construction started yesterday morning on five countries'
special exhibition gardens -- those of Britain, Egypt, Japan,
Finland and Russia. 
</P>
