<HEADLINE> Missing Plane Found Crashed in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 25 (Xinhua) -- A passenger plane missing
since last Friday morning was Tuesday morning found crashed at an
altitude of 12,000 feet (some 4,000 meters), an airport officer
said.
</P>
<P>
The plane was found "crashed and in pieces," the officer at the
Rescue and Coordination Center of the capital's Tribhuvan
International Airport said.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which had 18 people on board when it lost contact
five days ago, was first spotted by the pilot of an army
helicopter on the western side of Mt. Annapurna I.
</P>
<P>
But the officer said nothing about the situation of the people
on board. 
