<HEADLINE> Ukraine Calls for Support of Chernomyrdin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine President Leonid Danilovich
Kuchma Monday called on Russia's State Duma to support the
reappointment of Victor Chernomyrdin as the federal prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma's remark was made to the Ukrainian Interfax Agency. He
added that what has happened in Russia affirms the importance of a
"powerful and stable government."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an anonymous senior official in the Ukrainian
President's Office stated that he hoped "Chernomyrdin's rich
economic and political experience will help find the way out of
the economic crisis."
</P>
<P>
Ukraine pays close attention to Russia's economic situation
because the financial crisis occurring in that country could also
have negative effects upon it, he said.
</P>
<P>
Former Russian Prime Minister Chernomyrdin, sacked five months
ago, was back in power Monday following a surprise announcement by
President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin is facing one of the worst economic crises to
confront Russia since the Soviet collapse.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin urged the parliament to support his decision to dismiss
the cabinet of Sergei Kiriyenko and named Chernomyrdin as interim
prime minister on Monday. 
</P>
