<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Technicians to Train At German Volkswagen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-one scientific research
workers from Shanghai Volkswagen Automotive Company Ltd. will fly
to Germany late this month to receive a three-year training on car
design and development at the Volkswagen parent company.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that Chinese technicians will be engaged
in the design and development of new car models abroad, which is
an unusual step on the part of Volkswagen as the Germany comapny
used to keep the process a secret.
</P>
<P>
Huang Jirong, manager of Personnel Training Department at
Shanghai Volkswagen said that he believes Volkswagen's opening up
of this sector to Chinese technicians fully demonstrates the
sincerity of the company's cooperation with China and its
determination to pursue long-term expansion in the country.
</P>
<P>
Founded 13 years ago, Shanghai Volkswagen Automobile Company
Ltd. is widely considered the starting point of China's modern
car-manufacturing industry.
</P>
<P>
With a designed annual production capacity of 300,000 units,
the Sino-German joint venture has so far produced one million
Santana cars, about 50 percent of China's car market
share.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture chalked up 26.3 billion yuan in car sales in
1997 and placed high among the 500 major overseas-financed
enterprises in China for six years in a row. It is also the most
profitable of all the Volkswagen global joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
Peter Loew, deputy general manager of Shanghai Volkswagen, said
German Volkswagen Group has been implementing a global strategy
for car designing, purchasing of spare parts, production and
marketing, and that it values cooperation with China and is
willing to help Shanghai Volkswagen attain the level of scientific
research and development of the parent company by training senior
technical workers to become part of Volkswagen's round-the-clock
car development and designing link.
</P>
<P>
According to agreement, German Volkswagen will train 42 senior
technicians for its Shanghai Volkswagen. The second group of the
trainees will leave for Germany soon.
</P>
<P>
In tandem with personnel training, Shanghai Volkswagen has
accelerated expansion of a technical center, and is building a car
testing ground at a cost of 1.6 billion yuan. The car testing
ground will become China's first modern car testing
facility. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
