<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jayasinghe Cleared of Doping Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's top sprinter
Susanthika Jayasinghe has had her indefinite suspension lifted by
the International Amateur Athletic Federation (IAAF), state radio
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Sri lanka Broadcasting Corporation said the IAAF has
lifted the ban subject to Jayasinghe undergoing tests for banned
steroids every three months.
</P>
<P>
Last month she was cleared of doping charges in a 2-1 vote by
a three-member panel appointed here on the request of the IAAF
but there had been no word from the sport's governing body about
the final ruling on Jayasinghe.
</P>
<P>
Jayasinghe was banned by the IAAF in April after samples
showed she had taken a banned steroid, Nandrolone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
