<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Names Squad for Angola Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe have named a
full-strength squad for Sunday's Cosafa Cup soccer match against
Angola.
</P>
<P>
Victory for Zimbabwe would secure the southern African
championship, with a game to spare, from champions Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Coach Roy Barreto on Monday announced an 18-man team.
</P>
<P>
Goalkeepers: Abdul Karim (Caps United), Muzondiwa
Mugadza(Dynamos)
</P>
<P>
Defenders: Edelbert Dinha (Seven Stars, South Africa), Henry
McKop (Mamelodi Sundowns, South Africa), Dumisani Mpofu (Caps
United), Chamu Musanhu (Dynamos), Francis Shonhai (AmaZulu,South
Africa)
</P>
<P>
Midfielders: Patrick Daka (Amazulu Bulawayo), Norman
Mapeza(Dardanelspor, Turkey), Robson Muchichwa (Kaizer Chiefs,
South Africa), Shephard Muradzikwa (Arcadia United), Benjamin
Nkonjera(Amazulu Bulawayo), Kingstone Rinemhota (Lancashire Steel)
</P>
<P>
Strikers: Jonathan Chigwinya (Blue Swallows), Ian Gorowa(Cape
Town Spurs, South Africa), Tauya Mrewa (Hellenic, South Africa),
Adam Ndlovu (Delemont, Switzerland), Peter Ndlovu(Birmingham
City, England)
</P>
