<HEADLINE> China's Investment in Education, Culture Significantly up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- China put 21.66 billion yuan in
the sectors of culture, education, health care, broadcasting and
social welfare in the first six months of 1998, increasing by 32.7
percent over the same period of 1997, according to the latest
figures from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the country invested 1.98 billion yuan in the
scientific research and poly-technical services, up 2.3 percent.
</P>
