<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade up in Shanghai's Pudong New Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Trade in Shanghai's
Pudong New Area reached 6.029 billion U.S. dollars during the
January-July period this year, a 21.9 percent year-on-year
increase.
</P>
<P>
That included 3.336 billion dollars in imports, up 25 percent,
and 2.692 billion dollars in exports, up 18 percent.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded businesses were the largest players, accounting
for 54 percent of the total trading. State enterprises came in
second with 45 percent, a slight rise from the same 1997
period.
</P>
<P>
The majority of imports are machinery and electronics products,
worth 2.075 billion dollars, nearly 40 percent more than the same
1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Exports mainly consisted of machinery and electronics products,
garments, and textile products.
</P>
<P>
During the seven-month period, third-party processing trade
amounted to 2.289 billion dollars, of which 1.261 billion dollars worth
of goods were shipped abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
