<HEADLINE> Central Chinese City Boosts Power Supply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Zhengzhou, capital of China's
Henan province, has started on a 1.6-billion-yuan project to
improve the electric-power grid in urban areas.
</P>
<P>
The three-year project will involve rebuilding equipment for
the existing 93.6-km, 110-kilovolt electric lines and transformers
for a total capacity of 943,000-kva, and a 10-kilovolt
distribution network.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to boost sales by 235 million yuan and
profits by 98 million yuan a year.
</P>
<P>
The power supply in Zhengzhou is expected to be 15 percent
greater when the project is put in use. 
</P>
</TEXT>
