<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, August 25 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The U.N. Security Council Monday joined the
regional calls for an immediate cease-fire and the start of
negotiations towards a peaceful settlement of the conflict in
Congo (Kinshasa).
</P>
<P>
The council, after informal consultations, expressed support
for the regional diplomatic initiatives including the one of South
African President Nelson Mandela as the current chairman of the
Southern African Development Community, council President Danilo
Turk of Slovenia told reporters. (UN-Congo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia's Communist leader Gennady Zyuganov said
Monday that President Boris Yeltsin will step down within the next
few weeks.
</P>
<P>
He told the local Ekho Moskvy radio Monday evening that Yeltsin
would have to resign "on health grounds", the Interfax news agency
reported. (Russia-Communists-Yeltsin)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- Sixteen civilians, including five
journalists, were sentenced to death in Sierra Leone Monday on
charges of treason for their role in a May 1997 coup in the West
African State, a report reaching here said. (SierraLeone-Deaths)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The U.N. Security Council on Monday adopted a
presidential statement, calling for "an immediate ceasefire" in
Kosovo, and urging all parties concerned to strive for a political
solution to the issue.
</P>
<P>
The presidential statement also urged the authorities of the
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia and the Kosovo Albanian leader to
"enter immediately into a meaningful dialogue" to find a
negotiated political solution to the issue of Kosovo.
(U.N.-Kosovo-Statement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BONN -- The German government has decided to seek new sanctions
against Belgrade along with its European Union partners in order
to force an end to the conflict in Yugoslavia's province of
Kosovo, a German government spokesman said Monday.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting on the Kosovo situation on Monday, the German
cabinet expressed "extreme concern" over the escalation of
violence in Kosovo, and especially from the Yugoslav side, German
government spokesman Otto Hauser said.
(Germany-Yogoslavia-Sanctions)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesian Armed Forces (ABRI) Commander Gen. Wiranto
said Monday he had decided to terminate the military career of
Lt. Gen. Prabowo Subianto, former president Soeharto's son-in-law
and a former commander of the Army's elite special forces unit --
Kompassus.
</P>
<P>
Wiranto also said two other senior Kompassus officers,
Maj. Gen. Muchdi and Col. Gen. Chariawan, would be relieved from
their structural positions and duties in the military.
(Indonesia-Commander-Drop Out) 
</P>
