<HEADLINE> Poland Backs Zakopane's Olympic Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Poland's government would back
Zakopane's bid to host the 2006 Winter Olympics, officials said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Leszek Balcerowicz announced the Cabinet
Economic Committee would give money to Zakopane's Olympic bid.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Finance Minister Jerzy Miller said holding the Olympics
in Zakopane would cost 850 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The IOC will choose the host of the 2006 Winter Games in June
1999. There are six bids so far: Zakopane; Sion,
Switzerland;Poprad-Tatry, Slovakia; Turin, Italy; Helsinki,
Finland, Lillehammer, Norway; and Klagenfurt, Austria, making a
three-country bid that includes regions of Slovenia and Italy.
</P>
</TEXT>
