<HEADLINE> Clinton, Gore Praise Sang Lan's Courage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 24 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton and
Vice President Al Gore have written to Sang Lan, praising the
courage and dignity she showed after her injuries, Xie Xiaohong,
vice president of the Chinese Gymnastics Association and Sang
Lan's guardian, told Xinhua in an exclusive interview Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sang Lan got seriously injured during the World Goodwill Games
which was held in New York from July 19 to August 2, 1998. She has
moved from Nassau Medical Center to Mount Sinai Hospital of New
York for recovery treatment.
</P>
<P>
In his letter to Sang Lan on August 5, 1998, U.S. President
Bill Clinton said he was very impressed by the courage Sang Lan
has shown in facing such a tough personal challenge.
</P>
<P>
Mr and Mrs Clinton expressed the hope that Sang Lan would grow
stronger with each passing day.
</P>
<P>
In his letter to Sang Lan on July 29, U.S. Vice President
Al Gore said Sang Lan's plight has captivated the United States,
and the American people are inspired by her courage and dignity.
</P>
<P>
Gore said the support and encouragement of Sang Lan's family
and friends would help her through this difficult period. Mr and
Mrs Gore wished Sang Lan a healthy and successful future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
