<HEADLINE> Security Council Urges Congo Cease-Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Security Council
Monday joined the regional calls for an immediate cease-fire and
the start of negotiations towards a peaceful settlement of the
conflict in the country.
</P>
<P>
The council, after informal consultations, expressed support
for the regional diplomatic initiatives including the one of South
African President Nelson Mandela as the current chairman of the
Southern African Development Community, council president Danilo
Turk of Slovenia told reporters.
