<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canadian Dollar Drops to New Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian dollar dropped to a
new record closing low of 64.55 U.S. cents Monday, down about a
quarter of a cent from Friday's close.
</P>
<P>
The dollar touched an all-time trading low of 64.50 U.S. cents
during the day. The Bank of Canada intervened at several levels to
shore it up.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian currency, like other resource-based currencies in
the world, has been on the constant decline even since the Asian
financial crisis broke out last year.
</P>
<P>
During the past six months alone, the dollar is reported to
have lost about 10 percent of its value against the strong U.S.
dollar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
