<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> The EU on Top of Romania's Trade Partners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Union continued
to rank first among Romania's trade partners, with 59 percent of
Romania's total foreign trade in the first five months of the
year, showed the latest official statistical data.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of foreign trade of Romania amounted to 7.88
billion U.S. dollars, up 3.8 percent compared with the same period
in the previous year. Export volume reached 3.37 billion U.S.
dollars, while import volume was of 4.51 billion U.S. dollars.
Thus, the commercial balance over the mentioned period indicated a
deficit of 1.14 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The EU countries were on the top of Romania's trade partners,
with 63.2 percent of Romania's total export trade and 56.0 percent
of its imports. Exports to the EU amounted to 2.13 billion U.S.
dollars, 11 percent up compared with the same period a year
earlier. Nearly half of Romania's total export trade was destined
to four EU countries, namely Italy, Germany, France and the United
Kingdom. Romania's imports from the EU amounted to 2.53
billion U.S. dollars, 19.9 percent up as against the period a
year ago. The first country in this field is Germany, with 766.2
million U.S. dollars in exports to Romania, followed by Italy,
764.2 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The statistical data also showed that Romania had a negative
balance in trade with almost all its business partners, except a
few EU countries such as Greece, the Netherlands and Portugal, as
well as certain countries of the Central and Eastern Europe,
namely Bulgaria, Yugoslavia and the Republic of Moldova. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
