<HEADLINE> Greek Security Forces Ready to Prevent Attacks on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Greek security forces were ready
to prevent any attacks on U.S. targets in the country, a Greek
government official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Greek government spokesman Dimitris Reppas said that the
security forces were ready to make every effort to thwart any
attempts at terrorist acts.
</P>
<P>
He described as top alert the measures taken to prevent any
attacks by Moslem terrorists in reprisal for the U.S. missile
attacks on targets in Sudan and Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the U.S. attacks in Sudan and Afghanistan, Reppas
said that Greece condemned phenomena of terrorist violence and was
in favor of cooperation among all to combat such phenomena.
</P>
<P>
He added that Greece was in favor of the integrity and
inviolability of borders and believed that in international life
the rules of international law should prevail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
